31 July 2017 Government Communications and Information System invites members of the media to a photo opportunity and brief remarks by Minister of Communication, Ms Ayanda Dlodlo at the start of the Cabinet Lekgotla tomorrow, 01 August 2017. The Lekgotla will be preceded by an ordinary seating of Cabinet.  The photo-opportunity and remarks will take place as follows: Date: Tuesday, 01 August 2017 Time:  10h00Venue: Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guest Important note:       There is a compulsory accreditation process which all journalists attending should adhere to.  Media who have not submitted their details as required will not be granted access to the venue. Kindly confirm attendance by sending your details to pheliswa@gcis.gov.za  BEFORE 15h30 TODAY using the table below. NAME SURNAME ID/PASSPORT MEDIA HOUSE CONTACT NUMBER EMAIL ADDRESS CAR REGISTRATION                      To access the venue, you will be required to produce your ID/Passport as well as a Press Card indicating the media organization you represent or a letter from the editor. Enquiries: Phumla Williams Cell: 083 5010 139 Issued by: Government Communications